From: Chad Monroe <chad@monroe.io>
Date: Mon, 02 Feb 2026 10:06:14 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: allow on-channel scan for DFS channels

On-channel scans don't require leaving the channel, so DFS radar
restrictions should not apply.

Signed-off-by: Chad Monroe <chad@monroe.io>
---
 net/mac80211/chan.c |    4 ++++
 net/mac80211/scan.c |    5 +++--
 2 files changed, 7 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/net/mac80211/chan.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/chan.c
@@ -665,6 +665,9 @@ bool ieee80211_is_radar_required(struct
 			continue;
 
 		chan = link->conf->chanreq.oper.chan;
+
+		if (req->n_channels == 1 && req->channels[0] == chan)
+			continue;
 		radio_idx = cfg80211_get_radio_idx_by_chan(wiphy, chan);
 
 		if (ieee80211_is_radio_idx_in_scan_req(wiphy, req,
--- a/net/mac80211/scan.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/scan.c
@@ -1279,8 +1279,9 @@ int ieee80211_request_ibss_scan(struct i
 				struct ieee80211_channel *tmp_ch =
 				    &local->hw.wiphy->bands[band]->channels[i];
 
-				if (tmp_ch->flags & (IEEE80211_CHAN_NO_IR |
-						     IEEE80211_CHAN_DISABLED) ||
+				if ((tmp_ch->flags & (IEEE80211_CHAN_NO_IR |
+						      IEEE80211_CHAN_DISABLED) &&
+				     tmp_ch != local->hw.conf.chandef.chan) ||
 				    !cfg80211_wdev_channel_allowed(&sdata->wdev,
 								   tmp_ch))
 					continue;
